result.execSummary:
The defendant Travis L. Young Jr. was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Travis L. Young Jr. is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Travis L. Young Jr. was found guilty of Possess Firearm-Adjudicated Deliquent of a Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(1m)(bm).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: If probation or extended supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.  This applies to all counts and financial obligations.

Obey all of the rules and regulations of supervising probation agent. 
**Pay supervision fees. 
Do not possess or consume alcoholic beverages and do not have alcoholic beverages within the residence. Do not possess or consume controlled substances, except by prescription. Do not be in taverns or on any premises licensed for the sale of intoxicating beverages, except restaurants or grocery stores. Submit voluntarily to random tests of blood, breath or urine. Participate in counseling deemed appropriate by your agent, which may include: alcohol/drug, anger management/DV counseling, psychiatric/psychological, AODA Assessment and follow-through with recommended treatment. Actively search for employment, be employed or attend an educational institution or vocational training program. 
**Pay all court costs including all applicable surcharges. 
Defendant is ordered to submit to a DNA sample & pay the surcharge, notice given to def. in court. May not have contact with Tayvion F and D.C., unless otherwise permitted by the court/agent. May not possess any weapons, including firearms.  Any violation of Extended Supervision shall be reported to the Court within 30 days and at least 30 days prior to the termination of the Defendant's Extended Supervision.

1:42 PM Attorney Daniel Joseph Tombasco in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant Travis L. Young Jr. in court, in custody.  Attorney Benjamin L Schwarz in court for Travis L. Young Jr. Clerk N. Nobile.
MINUTES: The State is ready to proceed with sentencing, but places a concern on the record. Attorney Schwarz advises the Court that he just learned about the State's concern this morning, but the DE would like to proceed with sentencing today. Sentencing arguments heard. Defendant is sentenced to 5 years in the WSP; 2 years Initial Confinement w/ 118 days credit followed by 3 years of Extended Supervision w/conditions; No contact with Tayvion F. or D.C. (D.O.B. 1/30/2006). Any violation of ES shall be reported to the Court within 30 days and at least 30 days prior to the termination of the DE's ES. DE is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. DE is not eligible for the Substance Abuse Program. Appeal Rights, Firearm Warning & Voting Acknowledgement given.
